d Freud, Michel Foucault, Judith Butler, Jacques Derrida, Jean-Luc Nancy, Adrienne Rich and Laura Mulvey), and introduces key terms. Each chapter also discusses contemporary cinematic texts.Key FeaturesExtends current accounts of Queer Theory by analysing its relation to our everyday livesProvides historical overviews of key concepts such as heterosexuality, sadomasochism and fetishismUp to date coverage of issues and debatesExamples are taken from contemporary popular cultural texts such as films, documentaries and art projects  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311078046840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147447294440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474472944423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474472944/original  a978-3-11-078046-8  Edinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK